cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE

The paper discusses the use of deep convolutional neural networks for speech emotion recognition, which falls under the categories of speech processing and affective computing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SD (Sound), followed by cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the use of neural networks, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence, making cs.AI a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of recurrent neural networks, which falls under the category of neural networks and learning, making cs.NE a possible sub-category as well.
